<paragraph id="8BB7368AD85EFFD13CB4FE0531B1F94A" blockId="11.[151,1058,446,556]" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">
D i a g n o s i s: The elytra are testaceous, the pronotum shows a broad black macula at middle that extends onto the pronotal arch, and the mesoscutellum is brown. This combination of characteristics will distinguish the members of this species from congeners. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D85EFFD13D59FDAC33E4F94D" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" box="[378,475,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Perilypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="970" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D85EFFD13D59FDAC33E4F94D" box="[378,475,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">Perilypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
SPINOLA was revised in 1977 (EKIS 1977).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD85EFFD13CB4FD8632C0F8D7" blockId="11.[151,1059,571,945]" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 10.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD85EFFD13EE8FD81311EF937" box="[715,801,571,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="970" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD85EFFD13FE1FD813623F937" box="[962,1052,571,593]" captionStart="Figs 274-277" captionStartId="96.[151,191,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[155,1063,200,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[155,1063,200,1502]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="Figs 274-277: Habitus; (274) Cregya fuscomacula; (275) Perilypus izabal; (276) P. schusteri; (277) P. virgulatus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746798/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">Fig. 276</figureCitation>
. Color: Testaceous, except antenna dark brown, pronotal disc with central black macula, mesoscutellum brown, metepisternum and metathoracic coxae castaneous, femora black at distal margin, tibiae, and tarsi brown, pygidium and 7 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D85EFFD13ED2FD3530C1F9FB" attach="left" box="[753,766,655,669]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">th</superScript>
sternite black. Head: Interocular depression broad, shallow, crescentic; frontal umbo prominent; cranium minutely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD85EFFD13D7BFD7433AAF982" box="[344,405,718,740]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) slightly serrate, antennomeres gradually increasing in diameter from scape to antennomere 11, funicular antennomeres filiform; eyes finely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 20/35). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD85EFFD13F28FCB33157F879" box="[779,872,777,799]" captionStart="Figs 163-170" captionStartId="79.[151,191,1521,1543]" captionTargetBox="[183,1039,199,1493]" captionTargetId="figure@79.[151,1059,199,1508]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="Figs 163-170: Pronota; (163) Artoadenus atrafinus; (164) Cregya triguttula; (165) C. biguttula; (166) Perilypus schusteri (167) Platynoptera potaro; (168) Pelonium erudiatum; (169) Parapelonides aodontus; (170) Isoparis cassidilis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746764/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="970">Fig. 166</figureCitation>
) transverse, very finely punctate; pronotal arch well defined; subapical depression well defined; side margins of pronotal proper strongly arcuate (PW/PL 78/70); elytra flat, pubescence short and profusely distributed throughout disc; small asetiferous punctures widely distributed on disc, epipleural fold laterally positioned (EL/EW 240/60). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
